<br>
You are still misunderstanding.  Under my proposed system you would be able to have the Focus II item AND use your best spells.   They would not be mutually exclusive.  The "nothing" refers to another item in that slot, not spells.  <br>
<br>
In other words, under a true parallel system, what you are stating is "I would rather have nothing and my best spells than some Focus II item and my best spells."    Which doesn't make much sense, you must admit. No one would be forcing you to choose between a Focus II item or your best spells.  Like Verant is now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 5:33:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: focus</span><hr size=1> "Casters in parallel" was not a good way to put it then. Aren't we looking for le mot juste? <br>
<br>
If there were a parallel system, I'd keep a Focus II item in my bag and use it situationally, like I've done with the rest of the crap. I have an Extended Affliction III item that I use situationally, for example. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 6:12:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: focus</span><hr size=1> Yep.  And those weren't my mots, either...:) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufarghen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farghen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/02 9:01:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.4est.com/eq/120x120.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: focus</span><hr size=1> Possible details for Scirocco's system (I can't speak for the man, but this is my understanding of what he is saying).<br>
<br>
Instead of all Focus items having the spell level cap, a focus item would work on all spells regardless of level.<br>
<br>
        Casting haste for example:<br>
                Level I = 10%<br>
                Level II = 20%<br>
                Level III = 30%<br>
<br>
Under that system, you could benefit from a level II item at level 60, but not as much as a level III item would benefit you.  Much the same way as a level 60 warrior can benefit from a FBSS haste, but not as much as CoF haste.<br>
<br>
The way they're implemented, you end up with level I items being virtually useless by level 35 or so, level II being virtually useless by 53ish.<br>
<br>
